19/09/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The EU, the UNHCR and the OSCE on Monday (18 September) urged several Balkan states to adopt urgent measures to resolve "all outstanding issues" concerning the thousands of people displaced by the wars in the former Yugoslavia. Meeting in Zagreb, representatives of the organisations called on Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Montenegro and Serbia to make good on an agreement they signed in 2005. 
In other news, the OSCE Mission to Tirana is hosting an international seminar on co-operation among NGOs in preventing human trafficking in Roma communities. Some 60 participants from 13 European states are attending. (Albanian News - 19/09/06; OSCE website, AFP - 18/09/06)
